Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:04.880
Story Recapped here. Today, I'm going to&nbsp;
explain a Fantasy film called "Enter the Void."&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:07.120
Spoilers ahead! Watch out and take care.

00:00:07.920 --> 00:00:13.520
A junkie named Oscar has been staying in Tokyo&nbsp;
for some time, but he refuses to get a real job,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:13.520 --> 00:00:17.440
so he has turned to drug dealing to sustain his&nbsp;
addiction. The illicit trade has also allowed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:22.080
him to save up some money to buy his sister,&nbsp;
Linda, a plane ticket to join him in Japan.

00:00:22.880 --> 00:00:26.400
While observing the sky from their apartment's&nbsp;
balcony, Oscar suddenly wonders what it would be&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:30.160
like to view Tokyo from above. Linda tells him&nbsp;
that she doesn't want to think about it because&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:30.160 --> 00:00:34.640
she fears falling to death. As Linda gets ready to&nbsp;
leave for work, Oscar shows her the Tibetan Book&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:34.640 --> 00:00:39.920
of the Dead, which he borrowed from his friend,&nbsp;
Alex. After taking a brief look at the book,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:39.920 --> 00:00:44.320
Linda warns Oscar that Alex will turn him into&nbsp;
a junkie and eventually convert him to Buddhism.

00:00:44.320 --> 00:00:48.400
After Linda leaves, Oscar lights up a pipe&nbsp;
while denying that he's turned into a junkie.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:48.400 --> 00:00:51.680
As he is tripping, his friend Victor calls him,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:55.760
asking Oscar to bring his share of the pills to&nbsp;
him at a bar called The Void. Still on the high,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:59.600
Oscar asks Victor if he could come over to his&nbsp;
apartment instead, but Victor insists on meeting&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:59.600 --> 00:01:03.360
at the bar. Victor hangs up before Oscar could&nbsp;
tell him that he'd rather wait for him at home.

00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:08.800
As Oscar tries to sober up to meet up with Victor,&nbsp;
Alex arrives at the apartment. Alex tells Oscar&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:14.000
that he saw his sister with a guy named Mario.&nbsp;
Oscar confesses that he hates the man and swears&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.760
that he would kill the baby if Linda ever gets&nbsp;
pregnant with him. Alex says he'd like to see&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:21.520
Linda, so Oscar tells him that they can visit&nbsp;
her, but they'll have to stop by The Void first.

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:26.320
Alex tells him that he doesn't like the place,&nbsp;
so he'll just wait for him outside. Alex sees&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:26.320 --> 00:01:29.360
the amount of drugs Oscar is bringing,&nbsp;
so he warns him that he's carrying too&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:29.360 --> 00:01:32.880
much. Alex advises him to ask Victor&nbsp;
to pick up the pills at the apartment,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:32.880 --> 00:01:36.400
but Oscar discloses that Victor refuses to&nbsp;
come because of what happened with his mother.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:36.960 --> 00:01:42.320
As they are heading out, Oscar asks Alex&nbsp;
if their drug dealer, Bruno, has something&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:42.320 --> 00:01:46.960
more potent than D.M.T. Alex warns him that the&nbsp;
substance will fry his brains. He advises Oscar&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:46.960 --> 00:01:51.120
to finish the Book of the Dead instead and wait&nbsp;
for his big trip when he dies. Oscar confesses&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:54.720
that he's still confused by the book, so Alex&nbsp;
starts explaining it as they walk to The Void.

00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:59.120
Alex asserts that people who die will get to watch&nbsp;
the moments of their life reflected in a magic&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:59.120 --> 00:02:03.280
mirror. Afterward, they'll float like a ghost with&nbsp;
the ability to see and hear everything happening&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:03.280 --> 00:02:07.040
around them, but they won't be able to communicate&nbsp;
with living people. Alex explains that there will&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:11.200
be doorways to higher planes of existence, but&nbsp;
most people refuse to leave. Those who stay&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:11.200 --> 00:02:14.480
will start having a bad trip, and their only&nbsp;
option to get out will be to get reincarnated.

00:02:15.120 --> 00:02:17.920
When Oscar asks him what happens&nbsp;
when people experience a bad trip,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:17.920 --> 00:02:20.800
Alex stresses that people will start&nbsp;
having nightmares, and all their fears&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:24.000
will be manifested until they wish they&nbsp;
never died. They'll have an opportunity&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.920
to escape their predicament when they see dark&nbsp;
yellow lights representing couples making love.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:27.920 --> 00:02:31.440
When they take a closer look, they'll get a vision&nbsp;
of a possible future life with them, and they'll&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:31.440 --> 00:02:35.320
be allowed to choose the kind of life that would&nbsp;
suit them best. Finally, they'll end up in a womb&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:35.320 --> 00:02:40.160
and get reincarnated. Alex explains that the cycle&nbsp;
will repeat until they manage to break out of it.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:43.440
Oscar is somewhat disappointed to hear that&nbsp;
the afterlife holds nothing better for people.

00:02:44.160 --> 00:02:47.920
As they get closer to the bar, Alex tells&nbsp;
Oscar that he can't wait to see Linda.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:47.920 --> 00:02:51.760
He tells Oscar to take good care of her, warning&nbsp;
him that he's posing a danger to her because he's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:51.760 --> 00:02:56.400
turning into a drug dealer. Oscar reminds Alex&nbsp;
that he's the one who introduced him to Bruno.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:56.400 --> 00:03:00.800
Despite that, Alex is still quite concerned&nbsp;
about Oscar, so he advises him to get a real job,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:00.800 --> 00:03:05.040
suggesting that he could work as a bartender or a&nbsp;
D.J. Alex also chides Oscar about his affair with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:08.320
an older woman, pointing out that there's&nbsp;
a lot of younger Japanese women in Tokyo.

00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:12.640
When they arrive at The Void, Alex tells him that&nbsp;
he doesn't want to watch him dealing drugs with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:12.640 --> 00:03:17.600
Victor, so he'll just wait outside. As Oscar walks&nbsp;
to the bar entrance, he tells himself that Alex is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:17.600 --> 00:03:21.520
a bigger junkie than him. When he sees Victor,&nbsp;
Oscar tells him that he brought his share of the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:26.400
drugs, but he's puzzled when Victor apologizes to&nbsp;
him. Before he could ask him why he apologized,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:31.440
the police burst into the room. Oscar immediately&nbsp;
runs to the toilet and tries to flush the drugs.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:31.440 --> 00:03:34.960
They keep banging on the door, so Oscar tells them&nbsp;
that he's got a gun and he'll shoot if they don't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:34.960 --> 00:03:39.280
leave. Soon, one of the cops fires his weapon&nbsp;
through the door, hitting Oscar in the chest.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:43.920
As he drops down to the ground, he starts to&nbsp;
wonder if he's dying. He fears that they'll&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:43.920 --> 00:03:47.280
send him to jail if he survives because&nbsp;
he still has some drugs on his system.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:47.280 --> 00:03:50.880
While watching the police check his vital&nbsp;
signs, Oscar tries to convince himself that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:54.560
he's still tripping on D.M.T. He starts to worry&nbsp;
about his sister as his heartbeat slows down.

00:03:55.440 --> 00:04:00.160
Soon, Oscar sees his dead body lying on the floor&nbsp;
as the police search his pockets for more drugs.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:00.160 --> 00:04:03.600
When he flies out of the bar, Oscar sees&nbsp;
Victor getting hysterical while the police&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:07.120
drag him to their car. Alex tries to find&nbsp;
out from the authorities what happened,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:07.120 --> 00:04:10.240
but they only tell him there was&nbsp;
an accident. When Alex asks Victor,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:10.240 --> 00:04:13.520
he learns that they shot Oscar and killed&nbsp;
him. Alex runs away when the police try to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:18.160
arrest him. He tries to enter a strip club,&nbsp;
but the guards stop him, saying it's private.

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:21.680
When Oscar wanders inside the club,&nbsp;
he finds Linda dancing on the stage.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:25.760
After the dance, she goes to the dressing&nbsp;
room and fools around with Mario, her manager.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:25.760 --> 00:04:30.560
When her cellphone rings, she tries to answer it,&nbsp;
but Mario puts it down. Alex leaves her a message&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:34.000
telling her that the cops killed her brother&nbsp;
at The Void while bringing drugs to Victor.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:37.360
Alex advises her to find out what happened&nbsp;
for herself because the cops are after him.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:41.680
Back inside the club, Oscar watches&nbsp;
Linda as she gets intimate with Mario.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:44.640
When Mario finally leaves her, Linda&nbsp;
listens to the message and starts&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:46.800
crying after hearing what happened to her brother.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:46.800 --> 00:04:50.480
Oscar starts recalling the moments with his&nbsp;
sister and their parents when they were children.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:50.480 --> 00:04:54.240
He soon relives when their parents died in a car&nbsp;
crash while they were on their way to a trip.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:54.240 --> 00:04:58.320
As the police investigate the accident, Oscar&nbsp;
tries to comfort Linda as she cries for their mom.

00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:02.960
Sometime after the tragedy, Oscar and Linda&nbsp;
make a pact never to leave each other.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:02.960 --> 00:05:06.000
They seal their promise by cutting&nbsp;
their thumbs and putting them together.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:10.160
However, the authorities soon take them and&nbsp;
send them to separate foster homes. As the Child&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:10.160 --> 00:05:14.320
Protective Services agent takes Linda away, she&nbsp;
calls out to Oscar, reminding him of their pact.

00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:18.800
Later on, Oscar is taken back to the&nbsp;
time before Linda joined him in Tokyo.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:18.800 --> 00:05:22.720
When Alex advises him to bring his sister to&nbsp;
Japan, Oscar tells him that he doesn't have enough&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:22.720 --> 00:05:26.800
money. He asserts that he could start dealing&nbsp;
drugs, but Alex tells him that it's too dangerous.

00:05:27.520 --> 00:05:31.040
When Victor invites him to have dinner at&nbsp;
their home, he learns that Victor's mother,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:37.200
Suzy, once made money by dancing at a strip club.&nbsp;
After dinner, Suzy offers to lend Oscar some money&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:37.200 --> 00:05:42.160
