00:05:42.160 --> 00:05:45.280
While he gets intimate with Suzy, Oscar&nbsp;
recalls being nursed by his mother.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:45.840 --> 00:05:49.680
Later on, Oscar remembers his mother promising&nbsp;
to watch over him from the sky when she dies.

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:54.000
As the days go by, Oscar starts offering&nbsp;
drugs to every local woman that he meets.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:54.560 --> 00:05:58.640
Soon, Oscar calls Linda and tells her that&nbsp;
he now has enough money for a plane ticket.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:58.640 --> 00:06:01.600
When Linda asks how he got the money,&nbsp;
he just tells her that he has a job.

00:06:02.400 --> 00:06:06.800
Oscar soon revisits the day Alex introduced&nbsp;
him to Bruno. Alex warns him to be careful&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:10.480
about taking drugs at Bruno's place because he&nbsp;
does nasty things to people when they're high.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:10.480 --> 00:06:14.480
When they get inside Bruno's flat, he buys some&nbsp;
acid and asks the dealer if he has D.M.T. On&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:14.480 --> 00:06:17.840
their way out of the apartment, Alex tells&nbsp;
him that D.M.T. only lasts for six minutes,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:17.840 --> 00:06:21.760
but it seems like an eternity. Alex explains&nbsp;
that it's the same chemical that is released&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:21.760 --> 00:06:25.360
in the brain when a person dies. He surmises&nbsp;
that dying would be the ultimate trip.

00:06:25.360 --> 00:06:28.480
Alex lends Oscar The Tibetan Book of the&nbsp;
Dead and tells him to read it before he&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:28.480 --> 00:06:31.920
tries D.M.T. Alex reveals that he&nbsp;
once had an out-of-body experience,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:35.360
but he got scared that he wouldn't be able to get&nbsp;
back to his body when he saw himself from above.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:39.920
Soon, Oscar fetches his sister from the&nbsp;
airport and takes her to an amusement park.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:39.920 --> 00:06:43.280
On the rollercoaster ride, he recalls&nbsp;
the accident that killed their parents.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:43.280 --> 00:06:45.680
They were left to their grandparents&nbsp;
after the internment, but they couldn't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:45.680 --> 00:06:49.200
stay with them for long. Child Protective&nbsp;
Services had to take them away because&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:52.080
their grandmother cannot take care&nbsp;
of them due to her health problems.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:52.080 --> 00:06:56.000
Not long after Linda arrived in Japan, Oscar&nbsp;
tells her that he dreamt about the accident again.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:56.560 --> 00:06:59.360
She tells him that it doesn't matter because&nbsp;
they'll be living like a family again.

