her pregnancy. Back at the club, Mario tells&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:08.320
the dancer that he likes Linda. He claims that&nbsp;
Linda told him she wants to have a baby with him.

00:10:09.040 --> 00:10:13.040
On the streets, Oscar sees Alex calling a&nbsp;
friend to ask for some money and a jacket.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:13.040 --> 00:10:15.200
He tells his friend to visit his roommate, Tito,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:15.200 --> 00:10:18.320
but he warns him against calling him because&nbsp;
the police might be tapping their phones.

00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:22.320
In Alex's apartment, Linda tells Saki&nbsp;
that he regrets going out with Mario&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:22.320 --> 00:10:26.000
and says she should've dated Alex instead.&nbsp;
Saki lets her know that Alex has called to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:30.160
tell them he's okay. Meanwhile, Oscar sees&nbsp;
Alex scavenging for food in the dumpsters.

00:10:30.720 --> 00:10:34.000
When Linda meets up with Mario, she learns&nbsp;
that she was fired from the club because the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:37.440
boss didn't like how she dances. Mario&nbsp;
tells her that he'll take care of her,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:37.440 --> 00:10:40.640
but Linda tells him that she would've taken&nbsp;
her own life already if she only didn't get&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:40.640 --> 00:10:44.240
the feeling that Oscar wasn't watching over&nbsp;
her. She wishes that Oscar would come back to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:44.240 --> 00:10:48.400
life. Mario tells Linda to stop hurting herself&nbsp;
and accept the fact that her brother is dead.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:48.400 --> 00:10:51.920
When Oscar enters Linda's head, he&nbsp;
finds himself waking up in the morgue.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:51.920 --> 00:10:54.800
The mortician notices that he's&nbsp;
awake, so he informs the police.

00:10:55.520 --> 00:10:59.680
As they prepare to take Oscar home, a detective&nbsp;
asks Linda to let the police know if Oscar can&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:04.560
speak. Inside the car, Linda tells Mario that the&nbsp;
man who woke up at the morgue is not her brother.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:04.560 --> 00:11:07.760
When Oscar tries to touch Linda, she&nbsp;
freaks out, so Mario punches him.

00:11:08.400 --> 00:11:12.000
When he checks himself in the mirror at&nbsp;
home, he sees a different face for a moment.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:15.280
But things appear to be normal when he&nbsp;
briefly closes his eyes and opens them again.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:15.840 --> 00:11:20.080
Later, he finds Alex in the tunnels writing&nbsp;
some graffiti on the walls. Alex notices him&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:24.320
and reminds him that he was cremated days ago.&nbsp;
When he remembers, Oscar ends up back in their&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:24.320 --> 00:11:28.240
apartment observing Linda and Mario. Linda&nbsp;
wakes up and tells Mario that she dreamed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:28.240 --> 00:11:32.240
that her brother was brought back to life in the&nbsp;
morgue. She confesses that she feels uneasy having&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:32.240 --> 00:11:36.160
Oscar's remains in the box, so she says goodbye&nbsp;
to him and dumps his ashes on the kitchen sink.

00:11:36.800 --> 00:11:41.360
